What:       	/sys/kernel/uwb
Date:       	September 2024
KernelVersion:  Linux version 6.1.75
Contact:    	Rajendra Varma <raj.varma@samsung.com>
Description:    This directory contains the information pertaining
			to the debug nodes corresponding to the UWB hardware.
			The data is discharged from the firmware of UWB
			chipset through the SPI lines to the HOST when the
			device driver module is loaded

What:       	/sys/kernel/uwb/fwversion
Date:       	September 2024
KernelVersion:  Linux version 6.1.75
Contact:    	Rajendra Varma <raj.varma@samsung.com>
Description:    This node in the uwb directory contains the information about
			the firware version that is currently flashed on to the
			UWB hardware. This FW version is retrieved from the
			chipset when the UWB specific kernel module is loaded.

What:       	/sys/kernel/uwb/devid
Date:       	September 2024
KernelVersion:  Linux version 6.1.75
Contact:    	Rajendra Varma <raj.varma@samsung.com>
Description:    This feature is used to retrieve the ChipID/DeviceID
			of the UWB hardware after the device driver is loaded.
			This information is obtained by parsing the ATR message
			emitted directly from the firmware loaded on the UWB chipset

What:       	/sys/kernel/uwb/bl1_flash_retries
Date:       	October 2024
KernelVersion:  Linux version 6.6.46
Contact:    	Rajendra Varma <raj.varma@samsung.com>
Description:    This feature is used to display the number of BL1 download/flash
			retry attempts that are made while the FW download. If no flash
			attempts are made then it displays -1, if the flash is successful
			in the first attempt then the value will be 0. For any number of
			subsequent retry attempts made, the corresponding retry count is
			displayed.

What:       	/sys/kernel/uwb/num_spi_slow_txs
Date:       	January 2025
KernelVersion:  Linux version 6.6.46
Contact:    	Hasan Awais <hasanawais@google.com>
Description:    This node is used to retrieve the number of SPI transactions
			that have lasted beyond a certain threshold, depending on packet size.
			The default leeway added is 1ms, and `spi_slow_tx_ms` may be provided
			as a module parameter when loading the UWB kernel module.

